#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:586
#, fuzzy
msgid "Clustering pipeline."
msgstr "Agrupamiento"

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:587
#, python-brace-format, python-format
msgid ""
"Build a participant × statement vote matrix (values in {-1, 0, +1}). Missing"
" votes are imputed with the statement mean so that sparse voters do not skew"
" the principal components. PCA (2 components) followed by sparsity-aware "
"scaling — participants who voted less are stretched away from the centroid "
"by √(N_total/N_voted) — then %(method)s clustering with cosine distance. k "
"is chosen by silhouette score over k ∈ [2, 10]."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:590
#, fuzzy
msgid "Consensus."
msgstr "Consenso"

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:591
#, python-format
msgid ""
"A statement is surfaced only if the Wilson 95%% score interval on overall "
"agreement clears 70%%, AND every opinion group’s own Wilson lower bound "
"clears 60%%. Raw percentages alone are never sufficient — 7/10 agreement is "
"not \"70%% consensus\" when its confidence interval starts at 40%%."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:594
#, fuzzy
msgid "Representativeness (what each group believes)."
msgstr "Lo que cada grupo cree"

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:596
#, python-format
msgid ""
"For every (group, statement) pair we compute the lift — P(agree | in-group) "
"/ P(agree | out-of-group) — run a one-sided Fisher’s exact test on the 2×2 "
"contingency table, and apply %(fdr)s FDR correction across all tests at "
"q=0.05. Only FDR-significant statements receive the ✓ badge; everything else"
" is marked \"suggestive only\"."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:599
#, fuzzy
msgid "Bridges and divisions."
msgstr "Divisiones genuinas"

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:600
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Bridges require mean cross-group agreement ≥65%% (or shared rejection ≤35%%)"
" with inter-group variance ≤0.15. Divisive statements use a pre-specified "
"omnibus test: permutation χ² across ALL clusters on each statement, with the"
" fraction of shuffled assignments as extreme as observed reported as the "
"p-value. FDR is applied to those omnibus p-values. Gap CIs use Newcombe’s "
"MOVER-Wilson (1998) Method 10. The pairwise Fisher p on the extreme pair is "
"surfaced as a small-sample guard on the displayed gap, not a simultaneous "
"test."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:603
msgid "Reproducibility."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:607
#, python-format
msgid ""
"This analysis was re-run %(runs)d times with different random seeds. Mean "
"Adjusted Rand Index between runs: %(ari)s (1.0 = identical, 0.0 = random). "
"Representative-statement Jaccard overlap: %(jac)s."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:609
msgid ""
"Stability metrics were not computed for this analysis. Re-running will "
"attach them."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:613
#, fuzzy
msgid "Limitations."
msgstr "📖 Citas"

#: app/templates/discussions/consensus_results.html:614
msgid ""
"Clustering is fit on the same votes used for group summaries, so inferential"
" quantities are exploratory, not confirmatory. Benjamini–Hochberg FDR is "
"appropriate under independence or mild dependence; many tests on the same "
"clustering are correlated, so treat q=0.05 as a practical screen, not a "
"tight bound. Divisive statements compare the two clusters with the highest "
"and lowest agreement on that statement — the Fisher p-value guards the gap "
"in small samples but is not a test of all pairwise cluster differences. The "
"interval on the agreement gap uses Wilson bounds heuristically; a Newcombe "
"interval would be tighter for a difference of proportions."
msgstr ""

