#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:181
msgid "🔥 Controversial"
msgstr "🔥 Controvertido"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:183
msgid ""
"Statements where the overall vote is split — surfaces disagreement in the "
"statement feed. The formal \"Points of Division\" panel on the analysis page"
" uses a stronger, cluster-aware test."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:187
msgid "🕐 Recent"
msgstr "🕐 Recientes"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:188
msgid "Newest statements first"
msgstr "Declaraciones más nuevas primero"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:196
msgid "Understanding Consensus Analysis"
msgstr "Comprender el análisis de consenso"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:201
msgid ""
"After enough participation (7+ users, 20+ votes), the system analyzes voting"
" patterns to:"
msgstr ""
"Después de suficiente participación (7+ usuarios, 20+ votos), el sistema "
"analiza patrones de votación para:"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:206
msgid "👥 Identify Opinion Groups"
msgstr "👥 Identificar grupos de opinión"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:209
msgid ""
"Users are clustered based on <strong>voting similarity</strong>, not "
"demographics. The system uses PCA (Principal Component Analysis) and "
"Agglomerative Clustering to find natural groupings."
msgstr ""
"Los usuarios se agrupan según <strong>similitud de votación</strong>, no por"
" demografía. El sistema utiliza PCA (Análisis de Componentes Principales) y "
"Agrupamiento Aglomerativo para encontrar agrupaciones naturales."

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:212
msgid ""
"Example: Group 1 might prioritize environmental concerns, while Group 2 "
"prioritizes economic growth—even if both have mixed political backgrounds."
msgstr ""
"Ejemplo: El Grupo 1 podría priorizar preocupaciones ambientales, mientras "
"que el Grupo 2 prioriza el crecimiento económico, incluso si ambos tienen "
"antecedentes políticos mixtos."

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:218
msgid "✅ Detect Consensus Statements"
msgstr "✅ Detectar declaraciones de consenso"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:221
#, python-format
msgid ""
"A statement qualifies as consensus only when the <strong>Wilson 95%% score "
"interval</strong> on overall agreement clears 70%%, AND every opinion "
"group’s own Wilson lower bound clears 60%%. Raw percentages alone are never "
"enough — 7/10 agreement is not \"70%% consensus\" when its confidence "
"interval starts at 40%%."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:224
msgid "These represent common ground that stands up to small-sample scrutiny."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:230
msgid "🌉 Find Bridge Statements"
msgstr "🌉 Encontrar Declaraciones Puente"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:233
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Statements where every group lands on the same side — either all agreeing "
"(≥65%% mean) OR all rejecting (≤35%% mean) — with low variance between "
"groups. Shared rejection counts as common ground too."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:236
msgid ""
"These are especially valuable for finding solutions that work for everyone."
msgstr ""
"Estas son especialmente valiosas para encontrar soluciones que funcionen "
"para todos."

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:242
msgid "⚡ Highlight Divisive Statements"
msgstr "⚡ Destacar Declaraciones Divisivas"

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:245
msgid ""
"Statements where different groups vote differently — measured by the gap in "
"agreement between the most- and least-agreeing groups. Significance comes "
"from a <strong>pre-specified permutation χ² test across ALL "
"clusters</strong>, not post-selection of extreme pairs. The gap CI uses "
"<strong>Newcombe’s MOVER-Wilson Method 10</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:248
msgid ""
"These reveal where dialogue is most needed. FDR-corrected results are marked"
" ✓; uncorrected results are shown as \"suggestive only\"."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:254
msgid "🔬 Statistical rigour"
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:257
#, python-format
msgid ""
"<strong>Wilson 95%% score intervals</strong> on every reported percentage — "
"no more \"100%% agreement\" from 2 of 2 votes."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:258
msgid ""
"<strong>One-sided Fisher’s exact test</strong> for representativeness (which"
" statements distinguish a group from everyone else)."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:259
msgid ""
"<strong>Benjamini–Hochberg FDR correction at q=0.05</strong> across all "
"cluster×statement tests (or Benjamini–Yekutieli for strict peer review under"
" dependence — configurable)."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:260
msgid ""
"<strong>Stability metrics</strong> (Adjusted Rand Index, Jaccard overlap) "
"computed over re-seeded clustering runs; analyses whose clusters are not "
"reproducible are withheld."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:261
msgid ""
"<strong>Limitations</strong> are called out in the methodology panel of each"
" results page: clustering is fit on the same votes used for group summaries,"
" so all inferential quantities are exploratory rather than confirmatory."
msgstr ""

#: app/templates/help/native_system.html:267
msgid "📊 Visualize with Interactive Charts"
